Groups and organizations
Organizations have many attributes that apply to individual actors: size, age, personality (think of corporate cultures), and history.
They perform actions and develop behaviors (organizational policies).
However, they can easily have parts broken off or added to without fundamentally changing them, unlike most individual actors.

Organizations have many attributes that apply to individual actors: size, age, personality (think of corporate cultures), and history.

However, they can easily have parts broken off or added to without fundamentally changing them, unlike most individual actors.
Organizations have goals, internal structure, technology, resources (human and material), surrounding environment.
